# Render Logs Access

When debugging production issues, you can query Render logs directly instead of asking the user to check them.

## Endpoint

```
GET https://pb-webhook-server.onrender.com/debug-render-logs
Authorization: Bearer Diamond9753!!@@pb
```

## Query Parameters

| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |
|-----------|------|---------|-------------|
| `minutes` | number | 30 | Fetch logs from last N minutes |
| `startTime` | ISO string | - | Specific start time (UTC) |
| `endTime` | ISO string | - | Specific end time (UTC) |
| `limit` | number | 200 | Max number of log entries |
| `search` | string | - | Server-side filter (unreliable - prefer local filtering with findstr) |

## Example Queries

**IMPORTANT**: 
- On Windows, use `curl.exe` (not PowerShell's `Invoke-WebRequest` which times out)
- The server-side `search` parameter can be unreliable - prefer fetching logs and filtering locally with `findstr /i`

```bash
# Recent logs (last 5 minutes)
curl.exe -s -H "Authorization: Bearer Diamond9753!!@@pb" "https://pb-webhook-server.onrender.com/debug-render-logs?minutes=5&limit=50"

# Best approach: fetch logs and filter locally (more reliable than server-side search)
curl.exe -s -H "Authorization: Bearer Diamond9753!!@@pb" "https://pb-webhook-server.onrender.com/debug-render-logs?minutes=30&limit=200" | findstr /i "INBOUND-EMAIL"

# Specific time window (UTC) - remember Render dashboard shows AEST, subtract 11 hours for UTC
curl.exe -s -H "Authorization: Bearer Diamond9753!!@@pb" "https://pb-webhook-server.onrender.com/debug-render-logs?startTime=2026-02-10T10:24:00Z&endTime=2026-02-10T10:30:00Z&limit=100"

# Search for errors (local filtering is more reliable)
curl.exe -s -H "Authorization: Bearer Diamond9753!!@@pb" "https://pb-webhook-server.onrender.com/debug-render-logs?minutes=60&limit=300" | findstr /i "ERROR WARN"
```

## When to Use

- User reports something isn't working
- Need to investigate webhook failures
- Checking if a feature is being triggered
- Debugging errors in production

**Do not ask the user to check Render logs manually** - query them yourself using this endpoint.
